.TH "platform_device_add_resources" 9 "platform_device_add_resources" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
platform_device_add_resources \- add resources to a platform device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" platform_device_add_resources
.BI "(struct platform_device *pdev "  ","
.BI "const struct resource *res "  ","
.BI "unsigned int num "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
platform device allocated by platform_device_alloc to add resources to
.IP "res" 12
set of resources that needs to be allocated for the device
.IP "num" 12
number of resources
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Add a copy of the resources to the platform device.  The memory
associated with the resources will be freed when the platform device is
released.
